A 14-year-old student, Franz Andersin, described the chaos during the shooting at a Finnish school.
The incident, the worst in the country's history, left eight dead, including classmates and the headmistress.
The shooter, a teenager, had posted a video online prior to the attack.
Police were puzzled by his motives.
The shooter, who admired Hitler and Stalin, had planned the massacre meticulously.
He ultimately took his own life after the rampage.
The tragic event has shaken the community, prompting condolences from the Prime Minister and a national day of mourning.
